Steps to follow to setup Git account on linux.

1. git config --global user.email "mailID"
2. git config --global user.name "username"
3. Create & clone a repo from github by clone cmd.
4. git init
5. Create whatever file/directory you require.
6. git add "file/foldername"
7. Goto Account-> Settings-> Developer Settings and create a Personal access toeken on github.
8. copy that token and use it while pushing code to remote repo in password field
9. git commit    #this saves in local repo
10. git push      #this saves in remote repo
11. To cache the access token
12. git config --global credentials.helper cache
